    {
      "id": "6ac59c59_70c72c88",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/portal/charts/portal-sdk/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 114,
      "message": "Oh now I get it;) It's an environment variable that contains the reference to other environment variable\n\nUnfortunately you trick is kind of bad from a security stand point of view. As far as I can see in the tomcat code:\nhttps://github.com/apache/tomcat/blob/1d97bbbd4f060c7c9ab39f12bc67fde3085f36ef/bin/daemon.sh\nThose options are just concatenated to the cmdline. The problem with that is that by default /proc/<pid>/cmdline is world readable which leaks the password to all other processes while /proc/<pid>/environ is readable only for owner of the process (or someone with PTRACE caps)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-21 15:19:42.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e39f839e_d3aa40d4",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "b5efa1b5_81a9e03b",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/portal/charts/portal-sdk/templates/portal-sdk-aaf-pv.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 1,
      "message": "really? Isn't it the a one big race condition?\n\nConsider the scenario where we have 2 PODs starting on 2 different nodes:\nPod1               Pod2\nremove old config\ninit_aaf\nsave cert to pv\n                    remove old config\nTry to use cert\nbut it doesn't exist\n                     init aaf\nfail\n                     save cert to PV\n                     Use the cert",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-21 15:19:42.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "03c91c82_b017dbd6",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a1564c71_9f83ee30",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/portal/charts/portal-sdk/templates/portal-sdk-aaf-pv.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 1,
      "message": "well it seems to be the way it's done today. \nBut your proposition would not work as POD2 couldn't start (PV is RWO)\n\nif it's in memory we wouldn't have this issue ;)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2319,
        "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
        "username": "sdesbure"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-21 16:46:35.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b5efa1b5_81a9e03b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
